                  <tr>
                     <td width="100%" align="left" class="TableCellHeading">RSS support for pushing news items to your doorstep</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td width="100%" class="TableCellHeading">
                        <p align="right"><i>By Richard Vowles,
                              April 27, 2004</i></p>
                     </td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                     <td width="100%" align="left" class="TableCell">For those who are wondering what the "rss feed" option in News is, it is a syndication mechanism that lets the news items
                        be pulled down to your desktop without you having to visit the web site to be kept up to date. A simple reader is at <a href="http://www.sharpreader.net/">Sharp Reader</a> - it requires .NET, but there are quite a few other readers around (I encourage other people to post suggestions). If there
                        are other areas that could benefit from RSS, please let me know and I will consider adding them.
                     </td>
                  </tr>
